+CHANGELOG.md:901:- Tightened sw_sampler end-to-end JSON diagnostic coverage (frac-0116c): `SwSamplerEndToEndTests.test_sw_sampler_source_and_runtime_harness_round_trip_json_diagnostic` in `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now asserts the round-tripped diagnostic carries exactly the canonical fourteen-name `defaults` set (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms`, `density`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate`, `out_bus`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send`) and exactly the canonical eight-stage `signal_chain` set (`grain_trigger`, `pitch_jitter`, `pitch_transpose`, `position_scrub`, `grain_buffer`, `envelope`, `dry_out`, `fx_send_out`) via set equality plus explicit length, lifting the round-tripped coverage from a six-of-fourteen / list-equality spot-check to exhaustive cardinality and content checks. The new assertions are additive — existing assertions and source/runtime behavior are unchanged — so they pass against the current code on first run; full validation (`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/`) remains clean (`4670 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean), startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`), and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
